name: Cattail Run - Grand Single Family Homes
description:
ABOUT THE HOME ENERGY RATING SCALE
The HERS (Home Energy Rating System) Index allows buyers to compare the relative energy efficiency of different homes. The HERS Index home energy rating is determined by an independent RESNET-certified home energy rater ("Rater"). The lower a home’s score, the more energy efficient it is in comparison to the HERS referenced home. For every one-point decrease in the HERS Index score, there is a corresponding one percent (1%) reduction in energy consumption as compared to a home with a HERS Index of 100. A home with a HERS score of 100 reflects a home built to 2006 IEEC Building Codes. See the bottom of this page for more information on HERS scores.

amenities.name: Cattail Run
amenities.description: Cattail Run is located adjacent to 85 acres of preserved parkland by the Potomac River.

amenities.name: Cattail Run
amenities.description: Cattail Run is located in Loudoun County, Leesburg, VA, situated between Battlefield Parkway and Edwards Ferry Road. The community is located just 1 mile off Route 7, which passes through the Dulles Tech Corridor. Cattail Run is 2 miles from the historic downtown Leesburg, 7 miles from Ashburn (12 mins), 18 miles from Reston & 25 miles from Tysons (31 mins), and 39 miles from DC. Dulles International Airport is about 20 minutes away & the Leesburg Executive Airport is about 10 minutes away.

amenities.name: Closeby Ida
amenities.description: Closeby is Ida Lee Park, which has both indoor and outdoor pools!

amenities.name: Leesburg has
amenities.description: Leesburg has many, many parks and trails! Get outside at nearby Red Rock Wilderness Overlook Regional Park, Ida Lee Park, Banshee Reeks Nature Preserve, Ball’s Bluff Battlefield Regional Park, Rust Nature Sanctuary, Elizabeth Mills Riverfront Park, and so much more! Children will enjoy the area’s many small parks with playgrounds along with the Leesburg Animal Park.

amenities.name: Cattail Run
amenities.description: Cattail Run is just 2 miles from downtown Leesburg which has a variety of unique restaurants and bars including Shoe’s Cup and Cork, Delirium Café, King Street Oyster Bar, Tuscarora Mill Restaurant, Lightfoot Restaurant, Senor Ramon Taqueria, Rebellion Bourbon Bar, The Wine Kitchen and SideBar. Just 2 miles away enjoy Conch at The Village at Leesburg along with The Anchor Bar and more!

amenities.name: Loudoun County
amenities.description: Loudoun County is home to many golf courses including: River Creek Club, Raspberry Falls Golf & Hunt Club, Algonkian Golf Course, The GolfClub at Landsdowne, the South Riding Golf Club, and more.
